  "response": "Melania Trump's wedding to Donald Trump on January 22, 2005, was a high-profile event. Here are the details regarding your questions:\n\n1. **Family Attendance**: Yes, members of Melania Trump's family attended the wedding. Her parents, Viktor and Amalija Knavs, were present, as was her sister, Ines Knauss. \n\n2. **\"Giving Her Away\"**: Traditionally, the bride is \"given away\" by a close family member, often her father. In Melania's case, her father, Viktor Knavs, walked her down the aisle as part of the ceremony.\n\n3. **Wedding Gown**: Melania Trump wore a custom-designed $100,000 Dior gown for her wedding. The gown was paid for by Donald Trump.\n\nThe wedding was an opulent affair held at the Bethesda-by-the-Sea Episcopal Church in Palm Beach, Florida, followed by a lavish reception at Mar-a-Lago.",
